  "*Latest 12 months. Source": "Market Guide via FactSet Research Systems.",
  "Coal's advantage over gas": "It's cheap. Utilities paid an average of $1.20 per million Btu for coal last year, compared with $4.30 for gas (delivered).   "Culpepper will probably need to undergo arthroscopic surgery this week on a sprained left knee that kept him out of the Vikings 27-24 loss to Detroit on Sunday.  \"It's a small scope, not a big deal at all,\" Minnesota coach Dennis Green said. \"Whether it's a 10-day injury or a two-week injury, you never know.\" Culpepper had been expected to play this week after sitting out last week.   "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=ANSI_X3.4-1968",
  "Culpepper will probably need to undergo arthroscopic surgery this week on a sprained left knee that kept him out of the Vikings 27-24 loss to Detroit on Sunday.  \"It's a small scope, not a big deal at all,\" Minnesota coach Dennis Green said. \"Whether it's a 10-day injury or a two-week injury, you never know.\" Culpepper had been expected to play this week after sitting out last week. He began the week listed as probable, but was downgraded to doubtful after his knee was still swelling and sore after taking some snaps on Wednesday and Thursday. He sat out of Friday's practice and was officially listed as inactive.     \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=1160\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLamar Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith carried nine times for only 22 yards at San Francisco. The rookie back is too inconsistent to rely on during the Fantasy postseason. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=133393\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003ePeerless Price\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR BUF - Grigsby \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePrice caught four passes for 67 yards against New England. He appears to be Buffalo's most reliable Fantasy player at this time. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=1011\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAlex Van Pelt\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB BUF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "o start during the Fantasy playoffs.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=146325\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJeff Garcia\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SF - Fear \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003egarcia left Sunday's game with sore ribs in the first half, then returned later. Tim Rattay played much of the second half in his place.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=235015\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eScotty Anderson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAnderson caught one pass for 69 yards against Minnesota. He will catch an occasional long ball, but Anderson is not producing enough to be useful for most Fantasy teams right now. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "om/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=187568\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDarrell Jackson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SEA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJackson caught four passes for 85 yards against Dallas. He continues to be one of the most underrated and reliable receivers in the AFC. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=133361\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonovan McNabb\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB PHI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNabb had a decent outing against Washington, throwing for 235 yards and two touchdowns. He did throw three interceptions as well, but McNabb will be a solid starter during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=187382\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eShaun Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "ption.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=1226\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntonio Freeman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR GB - McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe Titans limited Freeman to 42 yards on two catches. If your team is moving on in the playoffs, however, you can expect better numbers from Freeman in the weeks ahead. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=12404\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAhman Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen had an awful outing at Tennessee, finishing with just nine rushing yards and 24 receiving yards. Expect him to quickly rebound from such a poor performance. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "tent in recent weeks, but he still may be good for a few TD runs during the remainder of the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=187621\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Pinkston\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR PHI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePinkston left Sunday's game against Washington in the fourth quarter with a shoulder injury. He did not return to the contest, and finished with two catches for 77 yards and a score. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3435\u0026key=12363\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJay Fiedler\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e"

  "\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3213\u0026key=12375\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDoug Flutie\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SD - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChargers Head Coach Mike Riley said Monday that he plans to start Flutie Sunday against Kansas City instead of rookie Drew Brees.   "Holmes is likely to skip practice Wednesday and possibly Thursday due to a sore groin muscle.   "R\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3213\u0026key=1174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEddie George\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TEN - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/17/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGeorge was outplayed by Skip Hicks this week, but head coach Jeff Fisher has indicated there is no RB controversy.   "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 12/19/01",
  "The Bengals placed Smith on injured reserve with a hamstring injury Tuesday, officially ending his season. He will likely need surgery to reattach the muscle group in his hamstring to the bone. Jon Kitna will probably start in his place the rest of the season if he's healthy, but we don't recommend any Cincinnati quarterback the rest of the year anyway.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3213\u0026key=1177\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerry Allen\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe Ravens are likely to feature one running back Sunday against Cincinnati after Allen, Moe Williams and Obafemi Ayanbadejo combined for just 10 carries for 40 yards in Week 14. Allen is the likely starter of the three after he recovered from a hand injury. None of the three is a worthy starter in a Fantasy league regardless of whether he starts.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c!",
  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "Updated 12/17/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGadsden suffered a strained hamstring on Sunday.   "Gadsden (hamstring) might miss his second consecutive game this week. Chris Chambers may start in his place again. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3696\u0026key=12753\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFred Taylor\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB JAC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTaylor (groin) has returned to practices and is working with the scout team. He might appear in the team's final game, and is a longshot to play this week. He has missed too much playing time to warrant serious Fantasy consideration at this point of the playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3696\u0026key=1220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Graham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday. If Graham doesn't play, Trevor Gaylor will start in his place and Nate Turner will be signed off the practice squad. The Chargers are already missing their No. 3 receiver, Tim Dwight, due to complications of a collapsed lung. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3696\u0026key=1663\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntowain Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NE - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith rushed for a career-high 156 yards and a touchdown Saturday.   "Gramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday.   "\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cIMG HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2 WIDTH=14 HEIGHT=14 SRC=\"http": "//images.commissioner.com/images/eye_device_tiny.gif\"\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e\u003cFONT COLOR=\"#ffffff\"\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMake Selection\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e",
  "A banged-up Smith hasn't done much statistically in recent weeks. Don't depend on him during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=12431\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Hayes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHayes may step back into the forefront this week as the No. 1 wideout in place of Muhsin Muhammad. He isn't very explosive, however, and won't help Fantasy teams much during Weeks 15 through 17.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=235174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Weinke\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CAR - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Consider Weinke as a backup during the Fantasy playoffs. He lacks the weapons to post better-than-average numbers, but he is a good option if you need an emergency QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=12797\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKurt Warner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB STL - Hunter \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWarner should guide many Fantasy teams to success during the playoffs. Expect fine numbers from him the rest of the way.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year. He will be a key player on many title teams, and should never be benched. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Graham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday. If Graham doesn't play, Trevor Gaylor will start in his place and Nate Turner will be signed off the practice squad. The Chargers are already missing their No. 3 receiver, Tim Dwight, due to complications of a collapsed lung. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1663\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntowain Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NE - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith rushed for a career-high 156 yards and a touchdown Saturday. He has been one of the best runners in the AFC and will help carry your team to Fantasy glory.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "Gramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday. He hurt himself on a PAT attempt, but Gramatica is expected to play on December 29.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman is now listed as probable for Sunday's game. He should be able to start against the Jaguars, but he may play with some pain in his thumb. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1264\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJeff Graham\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SD - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c12647549.1075855351154.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Richardson hasn't been a consistent scoring threat this year. Don't use him during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=12400\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Gonzalez\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE KC - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGonzalez hasn't played as well as expected this year. Still, he is too talented to bench during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFavre has been one of the best QBs this season. Count on him to help lead your team to Fantasy glory.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD BGCOLOR=\"#e0e6df\" COLSPAN=5\u003e\u003cIMG WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 SRC=\"http": "//images.commissioner.com/images/dot_clear.gif\"\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003cTR BGCOLOR=#eaeaea \u003e\u003cTD class=TD2 \u003e\u003cB\u003eTOTALS\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003cTD class=TD2 ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cB\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003cTD class=TD2 ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cB\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003cTD class=TD2 ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cB\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003cTD class=TD2 ALIGN=right\u003e\u003cB\u003e0.0\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e",
  "Bouman is now listed as probable for Sunday's game. He should be able to start against the Jaguars, but he may play with some pain in his thumb. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=1264\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJeff Graham\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SD - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGraham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday. If Graham doesn't play, Trevor Gaylor will start in his place and Nate Turner will be signed off the practice squad. The Chargers are already missing their No. 3 receiver, Tim Dwight, due to complications of a collapsed lung. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=1663\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntowain Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Tue, 25 Dec 2001 10:50:20 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Garcia, whose practice time was limited all week, played in Saturday's game. He admitted afterwards that he has a cracked rib. He played with extra padding, saying it didn't greatly affect his throws. Garcia might not be at full strength in the remaining weeks but he will still be a solid No. 1 Fantasy QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=1174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEddie George\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TEN - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGeorge played in Saturday's game despite suffering from an ankle injury. He left in the third quarter because of a neck injury but returned to the game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=1612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eOronde Gadsden\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c2920871.1075855351262.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Minnis hasn't done much to help Fantasy owners this year. Don't use him during the remaining weeks of the NFL season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=1310\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMichael Westbrook\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWestbrook has been inconsistent this season as a Fantasy player. He will be a good No. 2 at best during your playoffs.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=235213\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Gardner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner has been very inconsistent this season. Unless you play in a deeper league, starting Gardner isn't advisable.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 12/25/01",
  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "Updated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWalls was able to play in Sunday's game despite an ankle injury, but he left the game before halftime after spraining his left knee. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=133297\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMartin Gramatica\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, K TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday. He hurt himself on a PAT attempt, but Gramatica is expected to play on December 29.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3769\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",

  "Hayes may step back into the forefront this week as the No. 1 wideout in place of Muhsin Muhammad. He isn't very explosive, however, and won't help Fantasy teams much during Weeks 15 through 17.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=235174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Weinke\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CAR - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConsider Weinke as a backup during the Fantasy playoffs. He lacks the weapons to post better-than-average numbers, but he is a good option if you need an emergency QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=12797\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKurt Warner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB STL - Hardtail Amigos \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",

  "Updated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner has been very inconsistent this season. Unless you play in a deeper league, starting Gardner isn't advisable.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=1471\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Richardson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB KC - FJS \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eRichardson hasn't been a consistent scoring threat this year. Don't use him during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=12400\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Gonzalez\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE KC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGonzalez hasn't played as well as expected this year. Still, he is too talented to bench during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Updated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHorn is once again performing like an elite Fantasy receiver. He is a must-start player during the final weeks of the NFL season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=188183\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMaurice Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB ATL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eA banged-up Smith hasn't done much statistically in recent weeks. Don't depend on him during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=12431\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Hayes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Warner should guide many Fantasy teams to success during the playoffs. Expect fine numbers from him the rest of the way.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Pink Panthers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year. He will be a key player on many title teams, and should never be benched. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=2993\u0026key=12576\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRandy Moss\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIN - Metz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMoss started off slow this season but has once again been one of the best wideouts.   "Garcia, whose practice time was limited all week, played in Saturday's game. He admitted afterwards that he has a cracked rib.   "Mason missed Tuesday's practice with a hip flexor injury.   "McNair will miss Tuesday's practice due to tightness in his lower back which hampered him during Sunday's game against Green Bay. The injury is unrelated to his 1999 surgery to repair a disc in his lower back, and he should return to practice on Wednesday. Provided McNair heals over the next couple of days, he's a safe start for Week 15.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3066\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eZereoue re-injured his sprained shoulder late in Sunday's game against Baltimore.   "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Evil Empire 12/20/01",
  "The Ravens are likely to feature one running back Sunday against Cincinnati after Allen, Moe Williams and Obafemi Ayanbadejo combined for just 10 carries for 40 yards in Week 14. Allen is the likely starter of the three after he recovered from a hand injury. None of the three is a worthy starter in a Fantasy league regardless of whether he starts.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=3066\u0026key=12375\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDoug Flutie\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SD - Metz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChargers Head Coach Mike Riley said Monday that he plans to start Flutie Sunday against Kansas City instead of rookie Drew Brees. While Brees is not expected to play, he may see some playing time in the Week 16 finale against Seattle. Flutie is a very risky player during the Fantasy playoffs, especially in light of the possibility he could sit in favor of Brees at any time!",

  "\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=4\u003eGiggles Player News\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=/mp/player-news\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1140\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Wheatley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, Reserve RB\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003e Updated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=4\u003eLatest NFL Player News\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1151\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Watters\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SEA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWatters has placed on injured reserve. He will not play again this season. Shaun Alexander will be the starter for Seattle's final three games. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=12409\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrian Griese\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB DEN - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGriese should be able to return from a concussion after the bye week. Jarious Jackson will be Denver's No. 2 QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=1?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e",
  "\u003cIMG WIDTH=1px HEIGHT=1px SRC=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/open_gif?splnid=6c9f5755f428de1a\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026email=081ea514660665d0486be3bd2d3ec7d3bf095a621938b58c\u0026sport=football\u0026vend=CBS%20SportsLine.com\u0026product=mgmt\u0026time=20011220\u0026type=ereport\u0026random=1680\"\u003e\u003cHR\u003e\u003cCENTER\u003eCopyright 2001 Commissioner.COM Inc and SportsLine.com Inc.\u003cBR\u003eYour site can be reached from \u003cA HREF=http://fantasy.sportsline.com\u003ehttp://fantasy.sportsline.com\u003c/A\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003eFB10SP\u003cBR\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e",
  "Attention Fantasy Fans!  Subscribe to \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/224/sffer1127sn.cgi\"\u003eThe Sporting News\u003c/a\u003e now and get 4 FREE issues! Hurry!\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",

  "Date": "Thu, 20 Dec 2001 03:27:39 -0800 (PST)",
  "Dillon's dislocated finger has improved, and he should be fine for this week. He is listed as probable for Sunday's game against Baltimore. Don't reserve him based on this injury, and only consider benching him based on the Ravens' strong rush defense.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1025\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eScott Mitchell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMitchell could get the start Sunday against Baltimore due to Jon Kitna's strained ligament in the middle finger of his throwing hand. Whether Mitchell or Kitna gets the call, we don't expect either QB to be worth starting in the most important weeks of the Fantasy season.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=133415\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAkili Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "Franks suffered ankle and tailbone injuries on Sunday. His current status is day to day. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1204\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eCurtis Conway\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SD - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/17/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConway injured his shin on Saturday against Oakland. His current status is day to day.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEddie George\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TEN - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/17/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGeorge was outplayed by Skip Hicks this week, but head coach Jeff Fisher has indicated there is no RB controversy. Hicks will continue to see some carries at George's expense, though. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Gramatica (knee) was placed on injured reserve. Rookie Cedric Oglesby will be Arizona's placekicker for the final three games of the season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eZereoue is listed as questionable this week because of a sore shoulder.  He might start at RB if healthy. He replaced Chris Fuamatu-Ma?afala and gained 73 yards Sunday.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1152\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJerome Bettis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Holmes is likely to skip practice Wednesday and possibly Thursday due to a sore groin muscle. He is no worse than questionable for Sunday's game against San Diego at this point, but keep an eye on his status before you consider using him this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=235069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBill Gramatica\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, K ARI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to the \u003cI\u003eArizona Republic\u003c/I\u003e, Gramatica will miss nine months after tearing the anterior cruciate ligament and medial meniscus cartilage in his right knee while celebrating a 42-yard field goal on Saturday against the New York Giants. The Cardinals will audition both Cedrick Oglesby and Vitaly Pisetsky on Tuesday to take Gramatica's place as the team's placekicker. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Mason missed Tuesday's practice with a hip flexor injury. His current status is day to day.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair (back stiffness) missed practice on Tuesday. His current status is day to day. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1306\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Sanders\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSanders has returned to practice from a back injury. He is not expected to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1471\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c7779710.1075855351977.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 12/20/01",
  "The Pittsburgh Steelers may be without Bettis for at least one more week. Two days after coach Bill Cowher said Bettis was likely to play Sunday against Detroit, the running back was listed Tuesday as doubtful with a groin injury. \"But this is not a Fred Taylor injury. He (Bettis) will come back and play this year. But we've got to be very careful making sure he's playing in the right games.\" Keep Bettis on your bench this week. His health status makes him too risky a player. Chris Fuamatu-Ma'afala will likely start for Bettis.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=12436\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSkip Hicks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTitans Head Coach Jeff Fisher said Monday that he plans to give Hicks more work over the final three games of the season, according to the \u003cI\u003eNashville Tennessean\u003c/I\u003e",
  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "Tony Richardson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB KC - Neal/McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eRichardson is day to day with a shoulder injury. He is expected to play on Sunday. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eOronde Gadsden\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGadsden missed Tuesday's practice with a strained hamstring. He is expected to play on Saturday.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=235069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBill Gramatica\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, K ARI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Updated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDwight (fluid in lung) is not expected to play this week. He has not produced very much this year when healthy.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1140\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Wheatley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB OAK - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWheatley, who was not used last week, is expected to see some playing time in Week 15. He will probably not be used enough, however, to help most Fantasy teams. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1680\u0026key=1816\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDerrick Mason\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",

  "Brooks had a big game against San Francisco last weekend, throwing for 347 yards and two scores. He may be a bit inconsistent this season, but his potential to post huge numbers makes it tough to bench him, especially against a vulnerable Indianapolis defense.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1234\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eWillie Jackson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NO - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJackson put up a huge game against San Francisco last weekend, posting 11 catches and 167 yards receiving. He'll face a questionable Indianapolis squad that is vulnerable to the pass in Week 10, so starting Jackson this week is a solid option. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1440\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eStephen Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB WAS - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUp!",
  "Bubba Franks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFranks may not put up huge yardage numbers, but his seven touchdowns in eight games makes him a valuable Fantasy player. Unless you have a better option on your roster, Franks is the type of tight end that should start on a weekly basis.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1593\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBill Schroeder\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR GB - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSchroeder (ankle) is not listed on the NFL injury report, and is expected to start on Sunday against Atlanta. He's a solid play this week against Atlanta, whose secondary is vulnerable to strong passing teams like Green Bay. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026ra!",

  "HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1366\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErnie Conwell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE STL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConwell has had a few down weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is somewhat of a gamble. With the lack of depth at tight end around the league, however, starting Conwell is something many Fantasy owners will have no choice but to do. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1456\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRichard Huntley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CAR - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHuntley will be the likely starter this weekend against San Francisco, but don't be surprised if he splits carries with Nick Goings.   "Message-ID": "\u003c1084981.1075862019377.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Michael Westbrook\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWestbrook has been inconsistent this season, but he has caught three touchdown passes in his last four games. He'll face a Denver secondary this weekend that is vulnerable at best, so starting him in deeper leagues is worth considering. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=235213\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Gardner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner has been held in check in his last two games, catching only three passes for 38 yards.   "fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair's status is still in question for Sunday's game against Cincinnati due to an injured right thumb. He threw the ball during individual drills Friday, and according to published reports, is likely to play despite not being 100 percent. We don't recommend McNair this week as a result.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "gue=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad finally had a somewhat productive game, catching six passes for 75 yards against St. Louis. He's had some success in the past against this week's opponent, San Francisco, so starting him is a decent move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFavre has been one of the best Fantasy quarterbacks in the league this season. He'll face an Atlanta team on Sunday with a very vulnerable secondary, so be sure to start Favre this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=!",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/5/3/sffer1113ffr.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10",
  "mbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133448\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Williams\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NO - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWilliams is one of the better Fantasy backs in the league, and is a good player to use on a weekly basis. He'll face an Indianapolis defense that has been underachieving all season long, so Williams is a must-start.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133233\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAaron Brooks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NO - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "om=2762\u0026key=187528\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eReuben Droughns\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDroughns will likely split time with Lamont Warren in Detroit's backfield this weekend in James Stewart's absence. Neither back has much Fantasy value outside of deeper leagues, and starting them is a huge gamble. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1112\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLamont Warren\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWarren will likely start in place of the injured James Stewart on Sunday against Arizona. He's split carries with Reuben Droughns, and is only worth starting as a last resort in larger Fantasy leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random!",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "ted 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis has stepped up his play after beginning the season slowly. He's averaged 112 yards rushing over his last four games, and is once again emerging as a reliable Fantasy player. Give him the start in Week 10 against a Denver defense that is vulnerable to high scoring games. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1062\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Banks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBanks has played well of late, throwing five touchdowns in his last three games. He's got a good matchup this weekend against a Denver team that can be beaten through the air, but he's only worth considering in very deep Fantasy leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=!"

{

{
  "6-10 Day Bottom Line": "Variable conditions continue with a stormy pattern entrenched over much of the nation. Overall temperatures will be normal to cool with very wet conditions. NO strong Arctic air is expected.",
  "Bottom line": "No Changes - Overall US conditions will return to a more normal late fall/early winter pattern (no Arctic air) over the next 2 days. This pattern will persist through the end of the month.",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Sun, 18 Nov 2001 06:03:52 -0800 (PST)",
  "Details": "A strong storm will push into the West late next week and next weekend bringing heavy rain and snow and temperatures near to below normal. At the same time - the Midwest will warm toward normal with wet conditions developing. By early in the last week of November the strong western storm will push into the central U.S. bringing widespread rain and snow. Behind the system another surge of below normal temperatures will track from the Midwest to the South to the East.",
  "For the near term (1-5)": "Bottom Line - Cooler weather will bring temperatures below normal from the beginning through the middle of the week in the Midwest and from the middle through the end of the week in the East and South. The below normal event will last 3 to 4 days before normal temperatures return. The Rockies and West will be normal to above normal with cooling by the end of the week.",
  "From": "a..roberts@enron.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c10098098.1075862019895.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",

  "FONT SIZE=2\u003eHarris is out for Thursday's game against Denver due to a hamstring injury. Harris has been an unreliable Fantasy player and is only worth a roster spot in deeper leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026start=31\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Hayes suffered bruised ribs during Sunday's game against San Francisco. He may miss some practice time this week, but he's expected to play this weekend against Atlanta. The Falcons secondary is one of the worst in the league, so Hayes could turn into a good sleeper pick in Week 11. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=12423\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerry Hardy\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE ARI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHardy is expected to return to practice this week after missing three games due to shoulder injury. However, he is not certain to play on Sunday against San Diego. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1368\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJackie Harris\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE DAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"!",
  "Lockett, who suffered a rib injury last weekend against Denver, expects to play on Sunday against Philadelphia. However, the wide receiver has no real value as a Fantasy player at this point. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1062\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Banks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBarring any setbacks, Banks will start Sunday's game against Philadelphia. Banks, who suffered a concussion last weekend vs. Denver, hasn't been feeling any after effects of the injury and should be under center for the 'Skins. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen (abdomen) !",
  "Martin suffered a hamstring injury during Sunday's game against Dallas. He'll miss a few days of practice, but is expected to play in this weekend's game against Washington. Martin has no real value as a Fantasy player at this point. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=19\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Giants\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT NYG - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to the \u003cI\u003eNew York Post\u003c/I\u003e, cornerback Jason Sehorn's surgically-repaired right knee began giving him problems again this past weekend. In fact, the team was unsure that he'd be able to cover either Randy Moss or Cris Carter on Monday night, but he played anyway. If he continues to play on a bad wheel, you should consider starting any receivers opposing Sehorn the rest of the season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pla!",

  "T\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eTennessean\u003c/i\u003e says McNair's hand was sore when he arrived at the team's practice facility on Monday. His loss may adversely affect Jerome Bettis' statistics, because Bruener is widely regarded as the best run-blocking tight end in football.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1140\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Wheatley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",

  "rs\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1035\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eElvis Grbac\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eBaltimore Sun\u003c/i\u003e says there is no indication that Grbac will be replaced as the team's starting QB. Still, he is not performing well enough to start for most Fantasy teams.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=133276\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Driver\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDriver is still dealing with a thigh injury, and is expected to miss Thursday's game against Detroit. The reserve wideout has no real value as a Fantasy player at this point. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=3\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Ravens\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "s\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith (knee) will start on Thursday's game against Denver. \"I'm not 100 percent, but I'm healthy enough to do my job,\" Smith told the \u003cI\u003eDallas Morning Star\u003c/I\u003e. He'll struggle to post solid Fantasy numbers due to Dallas' horrid passing game, so bench him this week if at all possible.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=12431\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Hayes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "told the \u003ci\u003eDenver Post\u003c/i\u003e. \"If he can help our football team, he'll play. If he's in a situation where he can't perform at the level that we think can help our team, then we'll keep him out and put somebody else in.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=245054\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBenjamin Gay\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eCleveland Plain-Dealer\u003c/i\u003e says Butch Davis won't indicate how much Gay will play in the near future. \"We'll try to get him involved in some of the games,\" Davis said. \"We'll see.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=4658\u0026key=1765\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKevin Lockett\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e"
}

Brunell's status is still unclear for Sunday's game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=1151\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Watters\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SEA - McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWatters' shoulder has not sufficiently healed enough for him to practice, says the \u003ci\u003eSeattle Times\u003c/i\u003e",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Tue, 20 Nov 2001 16:42:46 -0800 (PST)",
  "FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBarring any setbacks, Banks will start Sunday's game against Philadelphia. Banks, who suffered a concussion last weekend vs. Denver, hasn't been feeling any after effects of the injury and should be under center for the 'Skins. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen (abdomen) is expected to return to practice on Wednesday at full strength. He's been inconsistent this season, and is best used when the matchup is favorable. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=1290\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerrell Owens\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SF - TayDang \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c27802422.1075862021234.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Owens suffered a sprained left knee and ankle during the overtime session of last weekend's game against Carolina. The injuries aren't considered serious, however, and Owens is expected to be in the starting lineup on Sunday Indianapolis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=133349\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eCecil Martin\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PHI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMartin suffered a hamstring injury during Sunday's game against Dallas. He'll miss a few days of practice, but is expected to play in this weekend's game against Washington. Martin has no real value as a Fantasy player, but he is a key blocker for Duce Staley. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=19\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Giants\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT NYG - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FO!",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Evil Empire 11/20/01",
  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "Wayne has a sprained knee ligament, and is doubtful for Sunday's game against New Orleans. Terrence Wilkins may have to start in his place.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=12612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJerome Pathon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR IND - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePathon (foot) is done for the season. He will be put on injured reserve. Reggie Wayne (knee) is also hurting, meaning Terrence Wilkins might have to be moved back into the starting lineup. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=12363\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJay Fiedler\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDave Wannstedt told the \u003ci\u003eMiami Herald\u003c/i\u003e there is no QB controversy surrounding Fielder and backup Ray right now!",

  "X-To": "Grigsby, Mike \u003c/O=ENRON/OU=NA/CN=RECIPIENTS/CN=MGRIGSB\u003e",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": "",
  "``That's kind of hypothetical,'' he said. ``Jay is the starter, and my only comment is we're going to get it squared away and play turnover-free football.''\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=1220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Fear \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMike Shanahan said he does not know if Smith (ankle) will be sufficiently healed to play in Thursday's game against the Cowboys. \"We'll get a chance to evaluate that during the week and see,\" Shanahan told the \u003ci\u003eDenver Post\u003c/i\u003e. \"If he can help our football team, he'll play. If he's in a situation where he can't perform at the level that we think can help our team, then we'll keep him out and put somebody else in.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=245054\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eB!",
  "actice this week after missing three games due to shoulder injury. However, he is not certain to play on Sunday against San Diego. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026start=31\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e",
  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/163/sffer1120t.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9",
  "m/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=8\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Cowboys\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT DAL - Hardtail Amigos \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eLinebacker Dexter Coakley, who was expected to miss two weeks due to a sprained knee, will likely get the start on Thursday after being out for just one game. He'll help keep Denver's running game in check, but don't expect his presence to give Dallas' defense added Fantasy value as a whole. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4147\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Pink Panthers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith (knee) will start on Thursday's game against Denver. \"I'm not 100 percent, but I'm healthy enough to do my job,\" Smith told the \u003cI\u003eDallas Morning Star\u003c/I\u003e",
