  "\u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/135/sffer1120tr.cgi\"\u003ehttp://www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/135/sffer1120tr.cgi\u003c/a\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1191\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDerrick Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlexander (ribs) has returned to practice. He is expected to start against Seattle.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=235122\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarvin Minnis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMinnis (ankle) is listed as doubtful for Sunday's game. Larry Parker may have to start in his place,\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=235256\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eReggie Wayne\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR IND - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, !",
  "Attention Fantasy Fans!  Subscribe to \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/224/sffer1120sn.cgi\"\u003eThe Sporting News\u003c/a\u003e now and get 4 FREE issues! Hurry!\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Benjamin Gay\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eCleveland Plain-Dealer\u003c/i\u003e says Butch Davis won't indicate how much Gay will play in the near future. \"We'll try to get him involved in some of the games,\" Davis said. \"We'll see.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1765\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKevin Lockett\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eLockett, who suffered a rib injury last weekend against Denver, expects to play on Sunday against Philadelphia. However, the wide receiver has no real value as a Fantasy player at this point. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1062\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Banks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eU!",
  "Brunell's nagging leg injury might sideline him for Sunday's game against Baltimore. He decided about two hours before last Sunday's kickoff that he couldn't play against Pittsburgh due to a strained right quadriceps. Jonathan Quinn has been preparing as if he will start the game, so right now you shouldn't count on Brunell this week as you set your lineups.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12753\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFred Taylor\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB JAC - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTaylor received a second medical opinion Tuesday that indicated his severe groin injury could keep him out up to three months and possibly the remainder of the season, according to the \u003cI\u003eFlorida Times-Union\u003c/I\u003e. The diagnosis was that the injury still has not healed and will need more time to become healthy, and in the meantime Taylor has developed pain!",

  "Patriots Head Coach Bill Belichick announced late Monday that Brady will remain the starting quarterback for the remainder of the season, barring injury. This relegates Drew Bledsoe to a backup role and makes him useless from a Fantasy perspective. Brady might have his hands full passing against the Saints on Sunday, but he is a fairly safe weekly starter otherwise.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=15\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Dolphins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT MIA - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDefensive tackle Daryl Gardener could miss the remainder of the season due to a fragmented disc in his back. He will miss at least one month to rest and rehabilitate the injury before being re-evaluated. Gardener's absence hurts the Dolphins' rush defense, which might be burned a little more by opposing running backs in the upcoming weeks.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FON!",

  "asn't been playing well of late, so giving Sanders some consideration in deeper leagues is advisable. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=133230\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDavid Boston\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ARI - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBoston has become one of the premier wide receivers in Fantasy Football. He's posted three touchdowns and 217 yards receiving in his last two games, and should have another solid game vs. San Diego in Week 11. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=187741\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTom Brady\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NE - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "ated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBarring any setbacks, Banks will start Sunday's game against Philadelphia. Banks, who suffered a concussion last weekend vs. Denver, hasn't been feeling any after effects of the injury and should be under center for the 'Skins. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen (abdomen) is expected to return to practice on Wednesday at full strength. He's been inconsistent this season, and is best used when the matchup is favorable. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1290\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerrell Owens\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SF - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, He!",
  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",

  "n his hip, a side effect of the injury. It's sounding more and more like Taylor will not play again this Fantasy season, although you should probably hold onto him until a final decision is reached, provided you have a deep enough bench.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith's sprained ankle was not healed enough for him to practice on Tuesday, and there is a real chance he might miss Thursday's game against Dallas. He suffered the injury Nov. 11, and aggravated it during Sunday's game. You should probably play it safe and keep Smith on your bench for this week. Temper your expectations for the entire Broncos' offense as well - the Cowboys' D isn't the pushover many believed it would be prior to the season.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "om=2125\u0026key=1360\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMark Bruener\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE PIT - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBruener will miss the rest of the season after undergoing shoulder injury. His loss may adversely affect Jerome Bettis' statistics, because Bruener is widely regarded as the best run-blocking tight end in football.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1140\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Wheatley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB OAK - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWheatley told the \u003ci\u003eContra-Costa Times\u003c/i\u003e he is no longer being bothered by a knee injury. He expects to play on Sunday.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=187582\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErron Kinney\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FO!",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "right now. ``That's kind of hypothetical,'' he said. ``Jay is the starter, and my only comment is we're going to get it squared away and play turnover-free football.''\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMike Shanahan said he does not know if Smith (ankle) will be sufficiently healed to play in Thursday's game against the Cowboys. \"We'll get a chance to evaluate that during the week and see,\" Shanahan told the \u003ci\u003eDenver Post\u003c/i\u003e. \"If he can help our football team, he'll play. If he's in a situation where he can't perform at the level that we think can help our team, then we'll keep him out and put somebody else in.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=!",
  "roster as an insurance policy if you can.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12632\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJonathan Quinn\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB JAC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eQuinn may have to start in place of Mark Brunell (quadriceps) again this week. Brunell's status is still unclear for Sunday's game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1151\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Watters\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SEA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWatters' shoulder has not sufficiently healed enough for him to practice, says the \u003ci\u003eSeattle Times\u003c/i\u003e"
}

  "\u0026nbsp;\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=home\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026\"\u003e\u003cIMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=absmiddle HSPACE=2 SRC=\"http://images.commissioner.com/images/wizard/win95/x.gif\"\u003e\u003c/A\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003cTR\u003e",
  ", QB CIN - Tomaski \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWe can't advise you use Kitna as he goes up against the Browns' secondary this week. Cleveland has been very stingy against the pass all year, leading the league in interceptions and ranking ninth overall in sacks.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1681\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eCorey Dillon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDefinitely get Dillon into your active lineup as he goes up against the Browns on Sunday. He has a great career record against Cleveland (678 rushing yards, five rushing TDs in five games). Dillon should remain in your active lineup week in and week out in any league.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026ke!",
  ", WR BUF - Fear \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThere's a good chance that Moulds will be inspired to have a good week against a solid Miami secondary after he voiced disapproval at his recent limited role in the Buffalo passing game. Pair that with the fact that he has a good history against the Dolphins (four TDs in last six games), and he might be worth using as a No. 2 or 3 receiver this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=235093\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEric Johnson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE SF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJohnson caught three passes for 34 yards last weekend against Carolina. Unless you play in a deeper Fantasy league, Johnson isn't really worth starting at this point.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026l!",
  ".sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1859\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames Thrash\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR PHI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJust when you think Thrash is reliable, he puts up two catches for 17 yards like he did last weekend against Dallas. Thrash will still be in the starting lineups of numberous Fantasy teams, but he's a gamble nonetheless. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=187386\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRon Dayne\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NYG - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDayne has been a serious disappointment for Fantasy owners in recent weeks.   "\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHorn is dealing with a number of nagging injuries, but he's been playing through them quite well. In fact, Horn has 14 catches for 247 yards and two touchdowns in his last two games, and is a must-start in Week 11 against New England based on his potential to post huge numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=235196\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMichael Bennett\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBennett is proving all the critics right who said he wasn't ready for the NFL style of game. He's been a huge Fantasy disappointment and is barely worth a roster spot at this point.   "Collins had a solid game yardage-wise against Minnesota, throwing for 321 yards on Monday night.   "EF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1262\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmani Toomer\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NYG - Hardtail Amigos \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eToomer caught five balls for 60 yards against Minnesota on Monday night, but he'll struggle to post similar numbers vs. Oakland.   "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Johnson has been a prime target for Tim Couch in the Cleveland passing game this season, and is now a very reliable No. 2 or 3 Fantasy receiver. Johnson is on a real hot streak and has a good career record against the Bengals, his opponent for this week, so get him into your lineup.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=133260\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTim Couch\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CLE - McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCouch has a decent track record against the Bengals (453 passing yards, four TDs), whom he will face on Sunday. There are plenty worse quarterbacks you could choose from, so if you're reaching to find a starter this week, give him a look.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=187401\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003ePeter Warrick\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1!",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c15842880.1075862021730.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Evil Empire 11/21/01",
  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "X-FileName": "MGRIGSB (Non-Privileged).pst",
  "X-Folder": "\\MGRIGSB (Non-Privileged)\\Grigsby, Mike\\Deleted Items",
  "X-From": "Commissioner.COM \u003cnoreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com\u003e",
  "X-Origin": "Grigsby-M",
  "X-To": "Grigsby, Mike \u003c/O=ENRON/OU=NA/CN=RECIPIENTS/CN=MGRIGSB\u003e",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": "",
  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "gue=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1292\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJ.J. Stokes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR SF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eStokes had a solid game last weekend, catching eight passes for 72 yards and two touchdowns against Carolina. He's been very unreliable overall, however, so starting him is still a risky move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=235216\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTravis Henry\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BUF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHenry had a very disappointing game against the Seahawks in Week 10, and will likely struggle again against the far-better Dolphins defense on Sunday. He has been far too inconsistent to merit using this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1011\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB!",
  "hing, and will throw at least two touchdowns against Tampa Bay's inconsistent secondary. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1633\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eO.J. Santiago\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSantiago catches the occasional pass for the Browns and could find the end zone every now or then. He's going up against a mediocre Cincinnati secondary, so maybe this is one of the rare weeks he scores. Only use Santiago if you're desperate for a tight end, however, as he rarely gets a big yardage total.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=133324\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKevin Johnson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CLE - The Rocks \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/163/sffer1120t.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9",
  "om=490\u0026key=1329\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eShannon Sharpe\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSharpe has been a very reliable tight end despite having just one receiving touchdown on the season. He got seven catches the last time he faced Jacksonville, and should get several in their Week 11 matchup. Get Sharpe into your active lineup every week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1514\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eQadry Ismail\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eIsmail has become the Ravens' lead receiver this season, and is quickly developing into a very reliable No. 2 Fantasy wideout. He is on a real hot streak and has a good history against the Jaguars' secondary. Make sure you get Ismail into your starting lineup this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "pdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWarrick has been catching a fair amount of passes this season, but hasn't provided stats worthy of using him on a weekly basis in a Fantasy league. His matchup against Cleveland on Sunday is unfavorable, so keep him reserved this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1212\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDarnay Scott\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CIN - Pink Panthers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlthough Scott has caught a touchdown pass in each of his last two games against the Browns, whom he plays Sunday, we can't recommend you use him this week. He has been far too inconsistent and a real disappointment from a Fantasy perspective.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=490\u0026key=1847\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJon Kitna\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "reports please to to the URL below": ""
}

  "=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eVan Pelt had another fine game, throwing for 309 yards, three TDs and one interception.   "Attention Fantasy Fans!  Subscribe to \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/224/sffer1120sn.cgi\"\u003eThe Sporting News\u003c/a\u003e now and get 4 FREE issues! Hurry!\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Carter saw extensive action on Sunday as Stephen Davis played through back problems. He carried 18 times for 56 yards, and is a good backup to have if Davis in on your Fantasy team. Davis has always been known to battle minor injuries.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1762\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eIsaac Byrd\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eByrd started in place of the injured Muhsin Muhammad on Sunday. He posted decent Fantasy numbers in Muhammad's absence, catching five passes for 69 yards in Carolina's 10-7 loss to Atlanta. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad missed!",
  "Chandler had a subpar game on Sunday, throwing for only 132 yards against Carolina. The Falcons chose to attack Carolina with their ground game, which was the reason for Chandler's poor Fantasy numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1191\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDerrick Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlexander caught two passes for 56 yards in his return from a rib injury. He was not open often, and Alexander may continue to be a Fantasy disappointment if he stays healthy.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eTransactions,\u0026nbsp;View\u0026nbsp!",

  "Date": "Mon, 26 Nov 2001 07:47:59 -0800 (PST)",
  "Fiedler threw for 262 yards, three TDs and no interceptions at Buffalo. His performance may have quieted talk of a QB controversy, but Fiedler is still too inconsistent to be a dependable Fantasy QB.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=133361\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonovan McNabb\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB PHI - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe Redskins held McNabb to 92 passing yards and 39 rushing yards, with no TDs or interceptions. Expect the Philadelphia QB to rebound quickly from such a quiet performance.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1859\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames Thrash\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR PHI - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThrash caught four passes for 32 yards against Washington. He is too !",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "In his return from a knee injury, Wheatley carried the ball five times for 17 yards. Zack Crockett was used more often in short-yardage packages, and Wheatley does not appear capable of starting for any Fantasy team in the near future. Even when he is fully healthy, he may not be able to take many carries away from Charlie Garner.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1663\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntowain Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NE - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith had 153 yards of total offense and two touchdowns against New Orleans.   "Message-ID": "\u003c6826584.1075862022095.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "NT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBrady put up huge numbers against New Orleans, posting 258 yards passing and four touchdowns. He?s become a pretty reliable Fantasy player, and his performance will likely keep Drew Bledsoe on the Patriots? bench for another week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon threw for 221 yards, three TDs and no interceptions against the Giants.   "Sanders left Sunday's game against San Diego after re-aggravating a hamstring injury. He was replaced by MarTay Jenkins, and did not return to the game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=734\u0026key=1196\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEric Moulds\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR BUF - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMoulds finally emerged from an extended slump, catching six passes for 196 yards and two TDs against Miami. He also lost a fumble, and Fantasy owners should still remember that Moulds has been a disappointment for most of the year.   "Despite his inconsistent play and 14 interceptions, Weinke's job as Carolina's No. 1 quarterback is secure. \"There've been quarterbacks who have gone on to be very successful that have gone through times like this,\" coach George Seifert told the \u003cI\u003eCharlotte Observer\u003c/I\u003e. \"Even though there are a number of these plays that haven't turned out and there have been disruptions in his play, I think, ultimately, it will be more beneficial than not.\" While he may be the starting quarterback in Carolina, Weinke isn't worth a roster spot in most Fantasy leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=1184\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFrank Sanders\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ARI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSanders, who left Sunday's game against San Diego due to nagging hamstring injuries, is questionable for the Cards' Week 12 matchup at Oakland. However!",
  "Driver, who has been inactive for three straight weeks due to a thigh injury, returned to practice on Monday. His status for Week 12 remains unclear, but he's not worth starting on your Fantasy team in any event. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=1499\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis, who has been out all year due to a hamstring injury, will likely find out what his status with the Packers will be this week. Depending on his health, the team will either activate him, place him on injured reserve or cut him altogehter. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=1116\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames Stewart\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Hunter \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helve!",

  "Moe Williams\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWilliams becomes the Ravens' featured back after the injury to Jason Brookins. If you play in a deeper league or are desperate for a running back, consider picking up Williams, although you shouldn't expect him to post great stats unless the matchup is very favorable.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=192266\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJason Brookins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eResults of X-rays on Brookins' foot revealed a fracture of a bone in his small toe, which will sideline him for at least four weeks and possibly the rest of the season. Moe Williams becomes the Ravens' starting running back, and might be worth adding to your roster in a deeper league.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "NT SIZE=2\u003eBengals Head Coach Dick LeBeau said Monday he has not yet made a decision on the status of Rackers, who missed two field-goal chances Sunday. He is 9-for-18 in field goals this season, and Jaret Holmes has been on the practice squad since Nov. 1. Rackers will likely retain the job for Sunday's game against Tampa Bay, but he's a very risky Fantasy starter based on his struggles.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=133415\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAkili Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBengals Head Coach Dick LeBeau said Monday that Smith might be promoted to No. 2 quarterback, according to \u003cI\u003eThe Cincinnati Enquirer\u003c/I\u003e",
  "Smith now has two sprained ankles, and is questionable for Sunday's game against Miami. If he can't play, then the Broncos might have to start Kevin Kaspar and Chris Cole at wideout, depending on Keith Poole's recovery from a rib injury.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=235220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames Jackson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CLE - Hunter \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJackson's ankle remains sore, and he will be re-evaluated Wednesday to determine his status for Sunday's game against Tennessee. Benjamin Gay and Jamel White would continue to split carries if Jackson can't go.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=187627\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eNeil Rackers\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, K CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003c!",

  "ca\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eStewart, who suffered a neck stinger in last Thursday's game against Green Bay, is expected to be available for Week 12.   "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "he is optimistic that he'll be available for the game. \"I'll be there,\" Sanders told the \u003cI\u003eArizona Republic\u003c/I\u003e. \"They're just real sore from doing a lot of running and jumping - normal wear and tear.\" In any event, keeping Sanders on your bench may be a good idea against the tough Oakland secondary. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=1183\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRob Moore\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ARI - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMoore (hamstring) was supposed to begin some light running last week, but he ended up doing nothing of the sort. \"He hasn't made a lot of progress,\" coach Dave McGinnis told the \u003cI\u003eArizona Republic\u003c/I\u003e. \"We're going to come to a point where we're going to have to make a decision.\" Moore, who has missed the entire season due to injury, could be placed on the injured reserve list this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/163/sffer1120t.cgi\"\u003e",

  "om/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=1504\u0026key=12181\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eStephen Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlexander, who has been hampered by a ankle injury, returned to action on Sunday. He didn't start, however, and may lose playing time to both Walter Rasby and Zeron Flemister for the rest of the season. Walter Rasby will continue to start in his place, but Zeron Flemister has emerged as the team's best receiving tight end with Alexander out. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eSeattle Times\u003c/i\u003e says Hasselbeck's season might be over. Mike Holmgren said he would only use him in an emergency this week, and the Seahawks coach may elect to have Hasselbeck use the season's final two games to rest his injured shoulder. Trent Dilfer will start at San Diego this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",

  "Gramatica sat out practice Wednesday, but is expected to test his injured leg on Thursday. Doug Brien and Brad Daluiso worked out Wednesday for the Buccaneers, who might sign one if Martin Gramatica can't kick against the Baltimore Ravens this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTrent Dilfer will start this week in place of Hasselbeck, whose separated left shoulder is too sore for him to play.    Coach Mike Holmgren said Wednesday that Hasselbeck aggravated the injury, which he's had since the third week of the season, against the New York Giants last Sunday.   \"There's a chance I might have him and he could play in an emergency-type situation, but he's pretty sore,\" Holmgren said.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "McCardell is listed as probable with a thigh injury. He should be able to start this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=235203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Chambers\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChambers is listed as questionable with an ankle injury. He practiced on Wednesday and should be able to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1288\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames McKnight\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcKnight is listed as questionable with an ankle injury. He practiced and is hopeful of playing this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "Save $.05 a gallon on the gas that keeps your car's engine clean. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/226/sffer1228c.cgi\"\u003eClick here\u003c/a\u003e to apply online.\u003cBR\u003e",

  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "Updated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHenry will sit out again this week with a sprained knee. Shawn Bryson will start for the second consecutive week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair missed practice Wednesday because of back pain.   \"I'm going to try to do some things tomorrow and hope it loosens up and not have as much pain as I had today,\" McNair said.   \"I'm not going to go out and try to force the issue. If it's still sore and still tight where I can't have all my mechanics right, I'm not going to force the issue.\"     The Titans listed him as questionable yet again Wednesday, but McNair likely will play \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Warrick, who was benched late in last week's game, is expected to start. He has been a disappointment this year and Fantasy players should not use him at this point of the postseason.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman (thumb) may attempt to practice late in the week. His status remains unclear for this week's game, and Spergon Wynn is available to start if needed. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=49699.10\u0026random=3837\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eNFL Reports,\u0026nbsp;Transactions\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e",

  "Alexander (leg) was placed on injured reserve, officially ending his season. Walter Rasby will continue to start in his place, but Zeron Flemister has emerged as the team's best receiving tight end with Alexander out. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=549\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eSeattle Times\u003c/i\u003e says Hasselbeck's season might be over. Mike Holmgren said he would only use him in an emergency this week, and the Seahawks coach may elect to have Hasselbeck use the season's final two games to rest his injured shoulder. Trent Dilfer will start at San Diego this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=549\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",

  "Gramatica sat out practice Wednesday, but is expected to test his injured leg on Thursday. Doug Brien and Brad Daluiso worked out Wednesday for the Buccaneers, who might sign one if Martin Gramatica can't kick against the Baltimore Ravens this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=549\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTrent Dilfer will start this week in place of Hasselbeck, whose separated left shoulder is too sore for him to play.    Coach Mike Holmgren said Wednesday that Hasselbeck aggravated the injury, which he's had since the third week of the season, against the New York Giants last Sunday.   \"There's a chance I might have him and he could play in an emergency-type situation, but he's pretty sore,\" Holmgren said.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Henry will sit out again this week with a sprained knee. Shawn Bryson will start for the second consecutive week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=549\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair missed practice Wednesday because of back pain.   \"I'm going to try to do some things tomorrow and hope it loosens up and not have as much pain as I had today,\" McNair said.   \"I'm not going to go out and try to force the issue. If it's still sore and still tight where I can't have all my mechanics right, I'm not going to force the issue.\"     The Titans listed him as questionable yet again Wednesday, but McNair likely will play \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football292.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=549\u0026key=1152\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e",
  "Jerome Bettis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - The Rocks \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBettis sat out Wednesday's practice, and indicated he might not play in the regular season's final two games. \"You want to take care of the injury first and if that means not playing, that means not playing,\" Bettis told the \u003ci\u003ePittsburgh Post-Gazette\u003c/i\u003e. \"But you want to make sure you're healed up. The team playing as well as it has played allows me the opportunity to get healthy.   "Updated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eMiami Herald\u003c/i\u003e reports Minor will get more work on offense this week.   "McNair was excused from practice on Friday due to a family illness.   "Wynn will start Sunday's game against the Green Bay Packers in place of the injured Todd Bouman.   "Fiedler has been added to Miami's injury report with a sore throwing elbow. He is listed as probable for Sunday's game against Atlanta, and is expected to start.   "Gramatica missed Saturday's game against Baltimore due to a leg injury.   "FONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThomason suffered a hyperextended knee during Sunday's loss to Washington. He missed practice on Monday, and is status for Week 12 is uncertain at this time. The reserve tight end has very little value as a Fantasy player. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=133276\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Driver\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDriver, who has been inactive for three straight weeks due to a thigh injury, returned to practice on Monday. His status for Week 12 remains unclear, but he's not worth starting on your Fantasy team in any event. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=1499\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FAC!",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c10602194.1075862026299.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Evil Empire 11/27/01",
  "To": "mike.grigsby@enron.com",
  "X-FileName": "MGRIGSB (Non-Privileged).pst",
  "X-Folder": "\\MGRIGSB (Non-Privileged)\\Grigsby, Mike\\Inbox",
  "X-From": "Commissioner.COM \u003cnoreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com\u003e",
  "X-Origin": "Grigsby-M",
  "X-To": "Grigsby, Mike \u003c/O=ENRON/OU=NA/CN=RECIPIENTS/CN=MGRIGSB\u003e",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": "",
  "asy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=192266\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJason Brookins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eResults of X-rays on Brookins' foot revealed a fracture of a bone in his small toe, which will sideline him for at least four weeks and possibly the rest of the season. Moe Williams becomes the Ravens' starting running back, and might be worth adding to your roster in a deeper league.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=1263\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eWayne Chrebet\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NYJ - Tomaski \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChrebret did not practice Monday because of a shoulder injury. However, \u003ci\u003eThe New York Newsday\u003c/i\u003e reports that he is expected to play in Sunday's game. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "er=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=1779\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKeith Poole\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Hardtail Amigos \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePoole has bruised ribs that will likely keep him on the sidelines for Sunday's game against Miami. If he can't play, Kevin Kaspar would start in his place, and the Denver passing game would further suffer.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=1220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Fear \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith now has two sprained ankles, and is questionable for Sunday's game against Miami. If he can't play, then the Broncos might have to start Kevin Kaspar and Chris Cole at wideout, depending on Keith Poole's recovery from a rib injury.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "game at Kansas City on Oct. 25. He was placed on injured reserve last week. James' rehabilitation is expected to take seven months. He is not expected to take part in either of the Colts offseason minicamps. Team president Bill Polian has not said whether James will be ready for the start of training camp.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=1254\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerry Glenn\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NE - The Rocks \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGlenn could be put on injured reserve if he doesn't recover from a hamstring injury soon. That would mean the end of his season, and perhaps the end of his Patriots career. \"I haven't reached it yet,\" coach Bill Belichick said Monday when asked when he would decide if the roster spot would be better spent on someone other than Glenn. \"But as each day goes by, it gets a little bit closer.\"    \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e!",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/163/sffer1120t.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9",
  "r league, dropping Alexander is advisable.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=12411\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAz-Zahir Hakim\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR STL - Metz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHakim, who is dealing with an ankle injury, played in Monday night's 24-17 loss to Tampa Bay. He had three catches for 29 yards in the game. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=235019\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKevan Barlow\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBarlow suffered a dislocated shoulder during Sunday's win over Indianapolis. \"It's throbbing,\" Barlow told the \u003cI\u003eContra Costa Times\u003c/I\u003e",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "will likely retain the job for Sunday's game against Tampa Bay, but he's a very risky Fantasy starter based on his struggles.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=133415\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAkili Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBengals Head Coach Dick LeBeau said Monday that Smith might be promoted to No. 2 quarterback, according to \u003cI\u003eThe Cincinnati Enquirer\u003c/I\u003e. \"If that's what they're going to do, maybe the Bengals need to get rid of me,\" Smith said, citing a desire to be traded if he's used in a mop-up role. He's not a recommended Fantasy choice, although it's important to note that he's now likely next in line if Jon Kitna gets hurt.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football210.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=ee\u0026owner=96876.9\u0026random=4861\u0026key=1177\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerry Allen\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e"
}

{
  "An ongoing process will be to drill into the various demand zones to gain a better understanding of specific drivers of that demand.  ie": "weather sensitive load, industrial load and related economic factors, etc...",
  "Cc": "Allen, Phillip K.; Smith, Matt",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Mon, 15 Oct 2001 08:10:45 -0700 (PDT)",
  "From": "Holst, Keith",
  "Jason Wolfe is facilitating data collection and interpretation for the PNW.  I will likely recruit Billianna to follow suit in the DSW.  Jason Huang is moving to Gaskill's group, however, he will still have some involvement in this project.  I still intend on recruiting an individual from the research group, but feel that it is best to have the other regions \"framed\" (ie": "model built) prior to bringing that person aboard.  His role will be to refine our technique and mathematics.",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c31136696.1075853111036.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Much of the needed data is already in place, however some work remains.  Our existing NWPL histories consist of a handfull of compressor flows; demand is calculated by subtracting the downstream flow from the upstream flow.  This \"rough\"  method works, but the downsides are": "(1) this calculated number includes changes in line pack and therfore true demand is hidden; (2) we are forced to break NWPL into arbitrary regions determined by the placement of compressors.  Jason W. is working on collecting flows at every meter on the pipe.  This will afford a much more accurate reading of true demand devoid of linepack changes and significantly better regression analysis will result.  Jason is also looking at a more meaningful way of dividing the pipe into demand zones.",
  "Sent": "Saturday, October 13, 2001 11:02 AM",
  "Subject": "West Fundies",
  "This effort is being led by Tori and supported by both Jay and myself.  Gaskill's staff will be providing most of the manpower.  The concept is to design a model which takes a methodical and scientific approach in forecasting": "(1) declines of existing production,  (2) increases due to drilling.",
  "To": "Grigsby, Mike",
  "Using externally provided production data, we are in the process of dividing production into zones of like characteristics.  Each zone will be identified by": "Basin --\u003e Reservoir --\u003e Formation.  Analysis will be done at the zone level to determine its unique depletion curve.  This curve will be extrapolated to forecast future production from existing wells.",
  "X-FileName": "MGRIGSB (Non-Privileged).pst",
  "X-Folder": "\\MGRIGSB (Non-Privileged)\\Sent Items",
  "X-From": "Grigsby, Mike \u003c/O=ENRON/OU=NA/CN=RECIPIENTS/CN=MGRIGSB\u003e",
  "X-Origin": "Grigsby-M",
  "X-To": "Holst, Keith \u003c/O=ENRON/OU=NA/CN=RECIPIENTS/CN=Kholst\u003e",
  "X-bcc": "",
  "X-cc": ""
}
